# StringProvider smoke: register, populate with files (tree-built
# from path components), exercise walk/stat/path/open semantics.
# Mirrors src/zvfs.py:710-770's StringProvider behaviour:
#   - root node lives at id 0 (always DIR).
#   - addFile splits "/" and creates intermediate DIR nodes.
#   - walk(name, parent) on a miss appends a NOTFOUND node.
provider string
addFile 0 /a/b.txt hello
addFile 0 /a/c.d world
addFile 0 /readme alpha
walk 0 a 0
walk 0 b.txt 1
stat 0 0
stat 0 1
stat 0 2
path 0 2
open 0 2
walk 0 missing 0
stat 0 5
open 0 5
